; Dracula -> Dracula Dusk -- canonical color map
; Strategy:
;   Surfaces: soft purple-dark, H:246-253 family, L:14-22% (≈original Dracula depth)
;   Foreground: H:40, S:4%, L:76% -- dim warm grey, reduced contrast for long sessions
;   Comment: keep hue ~225, S 27%->12% (recedes without vanishing)
;   Accents: same hue, chroma reduced 30-40%, same lightness
;   GTK selection pink override: see palette.gtk.map (second pass)
;
; Format:  #rrggbb=#rrggbb  (hex lowercase; patcher is case-insensitive)
; Comment: lines starting with ; are skipped; lines without = are skipped
;
; Run:     ./dracula-dusk.sh <theme-dir>

; -- Surfaces -----------------------------------------------------------------
#1e1f29=#1e1d2c   ; GTK header/panel bg  H:248, S:13%, L:14% -- deep purple-dark
#232530=#242232   ; OB secondary surface H:248, S:12%, L:16% -- dark layer (themerc)
#282a36=#272538   ; Background    H:246, S:10%, L:18% -- soft purple-dark (≈original)
#44475a=#302e45   ; Current Line  H:248, S:10%, L:22% -- subtle lift, barely-there
; NOTE: Selection and Current Line share the same token in most themes.
; GTK selected_bg_color (pink) is handled by palette.gtk.map second pass.

; -- Text ---------------------------------------------------------------------
#f8f8f2=#c8c5be   ; Foreground    H:40, S:4%, L:76%    -- warm dim grey, -blanc (NOT blue/purple)
#6272a4=#878ea1   ; Comment       H:225, S:27->12%, L:52->58%  -- muted, recedes; WCAG AA 4.56:1

; -- Accents: same hue, same lightness, chroma -30 to -40% -------------------
#ff79c6=#e890c3   ; Pink     S:100->65%  -- dusty rose
#bd93f9=#c1a6e5   ; Purple   S:89->55%   -- soft lavender
#8be9fd=#a1dce7   ; Cyan     S:97->60%   -- soft sky
#50fa7b=#73d68c   ; Green    S:94->55%   -- muted sage
#f1fa8c=#e1e79f   ; Yellow   S:92->60%   -- soft warm yellow
#ffb86c=#eab781   ; Orange   S:100->72%  -- muted amber (already warm, light touch)
#ff5555=#e17373   ; Red      S:100->65%  -- soft rose-red

; -- Qt5/Qt6: #ffRRGGBB (ARGB 8-digit, alpha-prefix used by qt5ct/qt6ct) -----
; The 6-digit entries above do NOT match these: the 'ff' alpha prefix sits
; adjacent to the color hex, so the word-boundary lookahead/lookbehind blocks
; the bare-hex pattern. These entries handle that explicitly.
#ff1e1f29=#ff1e1d2c
#ff232530=#ff242232
#ff282a36=#ff272538
#ff44475a=#ff302e45
